            <div class="topic-box">
                <h3>📊 Types of Data</h3>
                <p><strong>1. Quantitative Data:</strong> Numerical data that can be measured (e.g., height, weight, temperature)</p>
                <p><strong>2. Qualitative Data:</strong> Descriptive data that can be observed but not measured (e.g., colors, textures)</p>
                <p><strong>3. Categorical Data:</strong> Data that can be grouped into categories (e.g., gender, product types)</p>
                <p><strong>4. Time Series Data:</strong> Data collected over time intervals</p>
            </div>

