            <h2 style="color: #4ecdc4; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 2.5em;">🎨 Unit II: Visualization Design Principles</h2>
            
            <div class="topic-box">
                <h3>👁️ Visual Perception and Cognition</h3>
                <p>Visual perception is the ability to interpret the surrounding environment through light in the visible spectrum. Cognition involves mental processes such as attention, memory, and problem-solving that help us understand visual information.</p>
                <p><strong>Gestalt Principles:</strong></p>
                <ul style="margin-left: 20px; line-height: 2;">
                    <li><strong>Proximity:</strong> Objects close together are perceived as related</li>
                    <li><strong>Similarity:</strong> Similar objects are perceived as related</li>
                    <li><strong>Closure:</strong> We fill in gaps to create complete shapes</li>
                    <li><strong>Continuity:</strong> We perceive continuous patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>Common Fate:</strong> Elements moving together are related</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="diagram-container">
                <h4>🎨 Color Wheel and Theory Diagram</h4>
                <svg viewBox="0 0 400 400" style="width: 300px;">
                    <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="150" fill="url(#colorWheel)"/>
                    <circle cx="200" cy="200" r="80" fill="white"/>
                    <text x="200" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" fill="#2c3e50">Color</text>
                    <text x="200" y="215" text-anchor="middle" font-size="14" font-weight="bold" fill="#2c3e50">Wheel</text>
                    
                    <!-- Color labels -->
                    <text x="200" y="40" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#ff0000">Red</text>
                    <text x="360" y="205" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#00ff00">Green</text>
                    <text x="200" y="370" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#0000ff">Blue</text>
                    <text x="40" y="205" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="bold" fill="#ffff00">Yellow</text>
                    
                    <defs>
                        <radialGradient id="colorWheel">
                            <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#ff0000"/>
                            <stop offset="17%" style="stop-color:#ff00ff"/>
                            <stop offset="33%" style="stop-color:#0000ff"/>
                            <stop offset="50%" style="stop-color:#00ffff"/>
                            <stop offset="67%" style="stop-color:#00ff00"/>
                            <stop offset="83%" style="stop-color:#ffff00"/>
                            <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#ff0000"/>
                        </radialGradient>
                    </defs>
                </svg>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px; color: #555;"><strong>Color Schemes:</strong> Complementary (opposite) | Analogous (adjacent) | Triadic (three equidistant)</p>
            </div>

            <div class="topic-box">
                <h3>📐 Principles of Effective Visualization</h3>
                <p><strong>1. Simplicity:</strong> Keep it simple - less is more<br>
                <strong>2. Clarity:</strong> Make it clear and easy to understand<br>
                <strong>3. Consistency:</strong> Maintain uniform design throughout<br>
                <strong>4. Accuracy:</strong> Represent data truthfully<br>
                <strong>5. Relevance:</strong> Include only necessary elements<br>
                <strong>6. Accessibility:</strong> Make it understandable to all</p>
            </div>

